Class PutDependentObjectRequest

    As of 9.0

    public class PutDependentObjectRequest
extends PutRequest
    This request inserts or updates a record in the specified dependent object. A dependent object is a child of a base object. These can be configured in the schema manager of the Siperian Hub Console. The record key identifies the parent base object record, and the dependent source key identifies the child dependent object record.

    Required Parameters:

    • PutRequest.setRecordKey(com.siperian.sif.message.RecordKey) - RecordKey object representing the key of the parent base object record. This is the record that the dependent object record will be a child of.
    • PutRequest.setRecord(com.siperian.sif.message.Record) - Contains the data to be updated or inserted. The SiperianObjectUid field for the record (see Record.setSiperianObjectUid(String)) specifies the type and the name of the dependent object or put-enabled package used to identify the affected dependent object and constrain the fields that can be set. For additional details, see PutRequest.

    Usage Example:

    The following example creates a new dependent object record that is a child of the base object record with ROWID_OBJECT key 782 in the CUSTOMER_NOTE package. It is assumed that this package is based on the dependent object of NOTE that is a child of the CUSTOMER base object.

    PutDependentObjectRequest request = new PutDependentObjectRequest();
    RecordKey recordKey = new RecordKey();
    recordKey.setRowid("782");
    recordKey.setSystemName("SALES");
    request.setRecordKey(recordKey);
    request.setGenerateSourceKey(true);
    Record record = new Record();
    record.setSiperianObjectUid("PACKAGE.CUSTOMER_NOTE");
    record.setField( new Field("NOTE", "This is a very important
    customer.") );
    request.setRecord( record );
    PutDependentObjectResponse response = (PutDependentObjectResponse)
    sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    RecordKey, PutRequest, PutDependentObjectResponse, Serialized Form

    API Pair: PutDependentObjectResponse

    API Group: Data Update/Insert
